# Master Plan: Design Information Modelling (DIM)

This document serves as the single source of truth for the evolution of the 3D authoring environment in Standlo, transitioning from the legacy "Canvas" concept to the new **Design Information Modelling (DIM)** architecture. 

It merges the codebase-wide entity migration ([Canvas](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/zustand.ts#67-68) -> [Design](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/zustand.ts#70-131)) with the advanced performance and aesthetic goals of the Data-Driven Rendering (v2.0) engine.

---

## D-CODE (Design Code) & Standlo Design AI Architecture

## 1. Goal Description
STANDLO's 3D interface moves from a traditional CAD logic to a "Terminal-First" approach. Visual manipulation of the 3D scene (mouse dragging, transforming) will generate realtime `D-CODE` statements in the [DesignTerminal](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTerminal.tsx#20-444). 
Furthermore, an AI Agent (`standlo_design`) will be implemented as a Cloud Function / Skill. This AI will generate D-CODE arrays based on user text prompts and inject them into the Orchestrator, effectively "building" 3D booths procedurally. 

A core requirement is precision normalization: the entire app (state, API, firestore) must standardize on a 3-decimal floating point precision.

## 2. Global Precision Normalization (3 Decimals)

To guarantee exact structural replication across Cloud, DB, and Clients, all XYZ coordinates and rotations will be fixed to 3 decimals.

### Proposed Changes
#### [MODIFY] [functions/src/core/utils.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/core/utils.ts) (or similar core package)
Create a centralized coordinate normalizer utility:
```typescript
export const normalizeCoord = (value: number | string): number => {
    const num = typeof value === 'string' ? parseFloat(value) : value;
    if (isNaN(num)) return 0;
    return Number(num.toFixed(3));
};

export const normalizeVector3 = (vec: [number, number, number]): [number, number, number] => {
    return [normalizeCoord(vec[0]), normalizeCoord(vec[1]), normalizeCoord(vec[2])];
};
```

#### [MODIFY] `functions/src/api/gateway/orchestrator.ts`
Apply the normalization at the network boundary *before* writing to Firestore or broadcasting to other users in live sessions:
- Intercept incoming [updateNode](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/design.ts#288-311), [createNode](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/design.ts#266-286) payloads.
- Apply [normalizeVector3()](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/core/utils.ts#14-21) to `.position` and `.rotation` arrays.

#### [MODIFY] `/src/lib/zustand/designStore.ts`
Ensure the local client state also trims values to avoid React render mismatches between UI and Cloud.
- Update [addEntity](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/zustand.ts#169-178), [updateEntityPosition](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/zustand.ts#179-189), [updateEntityRotation](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/zustand.ts#190-200) to call [normalizeVector3()](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/core/utils.ts#14-21).

