## 4. `standlo_design` AI Skill & Generation Pipeline

We must define a semantic interface for an AI Agent that translates a prompt ("I need a 4x4 minimalist booth") into D-CODE structures, and injects it into the local Firebase Emulator.

### Proposed Changes
#### [NEW] `functions/src/ai/skills/standlo_design.ts`
Implement a specialized AI skill that leverages Genkit.
- **Input**: User prompt, available parts catalog context (retrieved from Pinecone/Vector DB).
- **System Prompt**: You are a master architect bot. You generate strictly formatted `D-CODE` arrays to assemble physical booths... 
- **Output Schema**: JSON Array of D-CODE strings:
  ```json
  [
    "@gen_wall1 #add /type_wall /x0 /y4 /z0",
    "@gen_wall1 #rotate /z90"
  ]
  ```

#### [NEW] AI Metadata Vectorization Pipelines
To prevent the AI from hallucinating objects (e.g. issuing `#add /type_fantasy_chair`), it needs a strictly indexed Catalog.
We will hook into the Orchestrator Pipeline system for creation events (`sketch-create`, `part-create`, `assembly-create`, `bundle-create`, `design-create`)### 2. AI Metadata Background Pipeline ([pipeline.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/pipeline.ts) & Admin UI)

**Goal**: Prevent locking the client and Orchestrator by running the Genkit LLM payload async. We strictly adhere to the `trigger_firestore` architecture configured via Admin UI tools.

- **Admin UI AI Skills (`http://192.168.1.48:3001/ai-skills`)**
  - We configure an AI Skill named `ai_vectorize` with a prompt template targeted to generate translations and tag data from standard D-CODE schemas.
- **Admin UI Pipelines (`http://192.168.1.48:3001/pipelines`)**
  - We configure native Pipelines (`part-create`, `assembly-create`) connecting `trigger_firestore` to an Action node.
  - Action is set to `actionType: "brain"`, `targetPath: "ai_vectorize"`.
- **[functions/src/orchestrator/pipeline.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/pipeline.ts) (UPDATED)**
  - Added support for `actionType === "brain"`.
  - When the Interpreter hits this node, it offloads the payload to the internal Brain gateway.
- **Seeding ([scripts/seedLocalAISkills.mjs](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/scripts/seedLocalAISkills.mjs) & [scripts/seedLocalPipelines.mjs](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/scripts/seedLocalPipelines.mjs))**
  - Contains all configurations so local setups trigger natively through the exact same interfaces without hardcoded logic.

#### [MODIFY] `functions/scripts/seed.ts`
- Create a test seed file `functions/data/ai_skills.json`.
- When running `npm run development`, automatically upsert the `standlo_design` AI Skill metadata into Firestore so the frontend can query it natively.

